  <h3 class="govuk-caption-l">Alex Smith | CRN: XX000000</h3>
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Risk predictor scores</h2>

  <div class="main-content">
    














  <div class="govuk-body" data-module="arns-custom-app-insights">
    <section class="bottom-border" data-test-id="predictor-intro" aria-labelledby="intro-heading">
      <h2 id="intro-heading" class="govuk-visually-hidden">
        Introduction to risk predictors
      </h2>

      <div data-test-id="predictor-intro">
        <p>
          We have developed and validated these risk predictors using real historical data about how often people who have
          been on probation get further sanctions.
        </p>
        <p>Someone gets a sanction if they:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>are convicted by a court and given a sentence (such as a fine, community order, discharge or prison)</li>
          <li>accept a formal caution from the police</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="govuk-inset-text">
  Source: undefined assessment, completed on undefined
</div>


    </section>

    
    <section role="region" aria-labelledby="arp-heading">
      
        <div class="predictor-header-wrapper">
          <h3 id="arp-heading">All reoffending predictor</h3>
          <div class="staticOrDynamicTag" data-test-id="arp-staticOrDynamic">
            <strong class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--grey">
  Static
</strong>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-4">
          <span data-test-id="arp-probability-statement">
            About 1 in 100 people (1.23%) with a similar profile to Alex will get a sanction for an
            offence they commit within two years. This puts Alex in the low risk band.
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="scale-wrapper"
             role="img"
             aria-label="A linear gauge chart showing the All reoffending predictor score is 1.23%. This is in the LOW band. Below 50% is low, 50% to below 75% is medium, 75% to below 90% is high, 90% to 100% is very high. This was last updated 01 January 2025.">
          






  




  




  


<div class="arns-scale-marker" data-test-id='scaleMarker'>
  <div class="arns-scale-marker-wrapper--low arns-scale-marker-wrapper arns-scale-marker-wrapper-position-1" data-test-id='scaleMarkerPosition'>
    
  <div class="arns-scale-marker__card" data-test-id="scaleMarkerCard">
    <div class="arns-scale-marker__card-top">
      <h3 data-test-id="scaleMarkerCardContent">Low</h3>
    </div>
    
      <div class="arns-scale-marker__card-bottom" data-test-id="scaleMarkerCardBottom">
        <p>1.23%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="arns-scale-marker__card-pointer" data-test-id="scaleMarkerCardPointer"></div>
    
  </div>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="arns-scale-bar arns-scale-bar--fourths" data-test-id="allReoffendingPredictor-scale">
  <div data-band-percentage-start="0%"
       data-band-percentage="50%" data-test-id='lowBand'>
    <span></span>
  </div>
  <div data-band-percentage="75%" data-test-id='mediumBand'>
    <span></span>
  </div>
  <div data-band-percentage="90%" data-test-id='highBand'>
    <span></span>
  </div>
  
    <div data-band-percentage="100%" data-test-id='veryHighBand'>
      <span></span>
    </div>
  
</div>

        </div>

        

        <div class="bottom-border">
          

<details class="govuk-details details--chevron-style" data-test-id="details-wrapper-all-reoffending-predictor" id="details-all-reoffending-predictor">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary" id="details-summary-all-reoffending-predictor" data-test-id="details-summary">
    <span class="details__chevron" aria-hidden="true" data-test-id="details-chevron"></span>
    <span class="details__toggle-text" data-test-id="details-toggle-text">
      <span class="details__show" data-test-id="details-show">
        Show details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-show-hidden-text"> for the All reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
      <span class="details__hide" data-test-id="details-hide">
        Hide details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-hide-hidden-text"> for the All reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
    </span>
  </summary>
  <section class="govuk-details__text"
           aria-labelledby="details-summary-all-reoffending-predictor"
           role="region"
           data-test-id="details-section">
    
          <h3>What this score predicts</h3>
          <p>
            The All reoffending predictor predicts the likelihood of someone getting a sanction for any recordable offence.
          </p>
          <p>
            It includes all sexual and all violent offences, but there are other risk predictors that are specifically
            designed to predict serious, violent and sexual offences.
          </p>
          <h3>How we calculate the score</h3>
          <p>We calculate the score using:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>static factors only, when we have limited information (a static score)</li>
            <li>dynamic and static factors, when we have more detailed information (a dynamic score)</li>
          </ul>
          
            <p data-test-id="arp-static-or-dynamic-factors">This score has been calculated using static factors only.</p>
          

          <p>Static factors are things which cannot be deliberately changed, and include the person's:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>age when they enter the community caseload</li>
            <li>current offence</li>
            <li>total number of sanctions</li>
            <li>length of offending history</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The person’s current legal gender also counts towards the static score.</p>
          <p>Dynamic factors are things that can change, and include their:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>accommodation status</li>
            <li>employment status</li>
            <li>relationship status</li>
            <li>history of domestic abuse</li>
            <li>regular activities that encourage offending</li>
            <li>drug use and motivation to tackle drug use</li>
            <li>alcohol use</li>
            <li>impulsivity</li>
            <li>attitudes that support or excuse criminal behaviour</li>
          </ul>
        
  </section>
</details>

        </div>
      
    </section>

    
    <section role="region" aria-labelledby="vrp-heading">
      
        <div class="predictor-header-wrapper">
          <h3 id="vrp-heading">Violent reoffending predictor</h3>
          <div class="staticOrDynamicTag" data-test-id="vrp-staticOrDynamic">
            <strong class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--grey">
  Static
</strong>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-4">
      <span data-test-id="vrp-probability-statement">
        About 1 in 100 people (1.23%) with a similar profile to Alex will get a sanction for a
        violent offence they commit within two years. This puts Alex in the low risk band.
      </span>
        </div>
        <div class="scale-wrapper"
             role="img"
             aria-label="A linear gauge chart showing the Violent reoffending predictor score is 1.23%. This is in the LOW band. Below 30% is low, 30% to below 60% is medium, 60% to below 80% is high, 80% to 100% is very high. This was last updated 01 January 2025.">
          






  




  




  


<div class="arns-scale-marker" data-test-id='scaleMarker'>
  <div class="arns-scale-marker-wrapper--low arns-scale-marker-wrapper arns-scale-marker-wrapper-position-1" data-test-id='scaleMarkerPosition'>
    
  <div class="arns-scale-marker__card" data-test-id="scaleMarkerCard">
    <div class="arns-scale-marker__card-top">
      <h3 data-test-id="scaleMarkerCardContent">Low</h3>
    </div>
    
      <div class="arns-scale-marker__card-bottom" data-test-id="scaleMarkerCardBottom">
        <p>1.23%</p>
      </div>
      <div class="arns-scale-marker__card-pointer" data-test-id="scaleMarkerCardPointer"></div>
    
  </div>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="arns-scale-bar arns-scale-bar--fourths" data-test-id="violentReoffendingPredictor-scale">
  <div data-band-percentage-start="0%"
       data-band-percentage="30%" data-test-id='lowBand'>
    <span></span>
  </div>
  <div data-band-percentage="60%" data-test-id='mediumBand'>
    <span></span>
  </div>
  <div data-band-percentage="80%" data-test-id='highBand'>
    <span></span>
  </div>
  
    <div data-band-percentage="100%" data-test-id='veryHighBand'>
      <span></span>
    </div>
  
</div>

        </div>

        

        <div class="bottom-border">
          

<details class="govuk-details details--chevron-style" data-test-id="details-wrapper-violent-reoffending-predictor" id="details-violent-reoffending-predictor">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary" id="details-summary-violent-reoffending-predictor" data-test-id="details-summary">
    <span class="details__chevron" aria-hidden="true" data-test-id="details-chevron"></span>
    <span class="details__toggle-text" data-test-id="details-toggle-text">
      <span class="details__show" data-test-id="details-show">
        Show details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-show-hidden-text"> for the Violent reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
      <span class="details__hide" data-test-id="details-hide">
        Hide details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-hide-hidden-text"> for the Violent reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
    </span>
  </summary>
  <section class="govuk-details__text"
           aria-labelledby="details-summary-violent-reoffending-predictor"
           role="region"
           data-test-id="details-section">
    
          <h3>What this score predicts</h3>
          <p>
            The Violent reoffending predictor predicts the risk of reoffending for all offences that are classed as violent.
          </p>
          <p>
            However, the <a href="#svrp-heading">Serious violent reoffending predictor</a>
            is
            specifically designed to predict the most serious violent offences. Because of this, the Violent reoffending
            predictor should be used to identify whether someone is likely to commit offences not covered by the Serious
            violent reoffending predictor, such as:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>actual bodily harm, common assault and aggravated assault</li>
            <li>robbery and assault with intent to rob</li>
            <li>arson not endangering life</li>
            <li>criminal damage not endangering life</li>
            <li>abduction of children</li>
            <li>intimidation</li>
            <li>breach of restraining order</li>
            <li>possessing or use of knives or offensive weapons offences</li>
            <li>public order and harassment</li>
            <li>resisting arrest</li>
            <li>disorderly behaviour</li>
            <li>drunkenness offences (not including those related to driving)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To check if a specific offence is classed as violent, go to the
            <a href="https://equip-portal.equip.service.justice.gov.uk/CtrlWebIsapi.dll/app/documents/C025AF635DB44965AC7B629E5538CB5B/master">
              full list of violent offences (EQUip)
            </a>.
          </p>
          <h3>How we calculate the score</h3>
          <p>We calculate the score using:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>static factors only, when we have limited information (a static score)</li>
            <li>dynamic and static factors, when we have more detailed information (a dynamic score)</li>
          </ul>
          
            <p data-test-id="vrp-static-or-dynamic-factors">This score has been calculated using static factors only.</p>
          
          <p>Static factors are things which cannot be deliberately changed, and include the person's:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>age when they enter the community caseload</li>
            <li>current offence</li>
            <li>total number of sanctions</li>
            <li>number of violent sanctions</li>
            <li>length of offending history</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The person’s current legal gender also counts towards the static score.</p>
          <p>Dynamic factors are things that can change, and include their:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>accommodation status</li>
            <li>employment status</li>
            <li>relationship status</li>
            <li>history of domestic abuse</li>
            <li>regular activities that encourage offending</li>
            <li>drug use and motivation to tackle drug use</li>
            <li>alcohol use</li>
            <li>impulsivity</li>
            <li>temper control</li>
          </ul>
        
  </section>
</details>

        </div>
      
    </section>

    
