<details class="govuk-details details--chevron-style" data-test-id="details-wrapper-serious-violent-reoffending-predictor" id="details-serious-violent-reoffending-predictor">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary" id="details-summary-serious-violent-reoffending-predictor" data-test-id="details-summary">
    <span class="details__chevron" aria-hidden="true" data-test-id="details-chevron"></span>
    <span class="details__toggle-text" data-test-id="details-toggle-text">
      <span class="details__show" data-test-id="details-show">
        Show details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-show-hidden-text"> for the Serious violent reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
      <span class="details__hide" data-test-id="details-hide">
        Hide details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-hide-hidden-text"> for the Serious violent reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
    </span>
  </summary>
  <section class="govuk-details__text"
           aria-labelledby="details-summary-serious-violent-reoffending-predictor"
           role="region"
           data-test-id="details-section">
    
          
          <h3>What this score predicts</h3>
          <p>The Serious violent reoffending predictor predicts the risk of reoffending for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>murder or attempted murder</li>
            <li>conspiracy to, soliciting, assisting or encouraging murder</li>
            <li>manslaughter</li>
            <li>wounding or inflicting grievous bodily harm (GBH)</li>
            <li>nonfatal strangulation or suffocation</li>
            <li>offences related to possessing or use of a firearm or imitation firearm</li>
            <li>aggravated burglary in a dwelling</li>
            <li>kidnap or false imprisonment</li>
            <li>arson endangering life</li>
            <li>criminal damage endangering life</li>
            <li>aggravated vehicle taking causing death</li>
            <li>blackmail</li>
            <li>other non-motoring offences endangering life</li>
          </ul>
          <p>It does not predict the following serious offences:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>cruelty to or neglect of children</li>
            <li>abandoning children under two years</li>
            <li>abduction of children</li>
            <li>terrorism offences</li>
          </ul>
          <h3>How we calculate the score</h3>
          <p>We calculate the score using:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>static factors only, when we have limited information (a static score)</li>
            <li>dynamic and static factors, when we have more detailed information (a dynamic score)</li>
          </ul>
          
            <p data-test-id="svrp-static-or-dynamic-factors">This score has been calculated using static factors only.</p>
          
          <p>Static factors are things which cannot be deliberately changed, and include the person's:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>age when they enter the community caseload</li>
            <li>current offence</li>
            <li>total number of sanctions</li>
            <li>number of violent sanctions</li>
            <li>length of offending history</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The person’s current legal gender also counts towards the static score.</p>
          <p>Dynamic factors are things that can change, and include their:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>previous and current weapons offences</li>
            <li>accommodation status</li>
            <li>employment status</li>
            <li>alcohol use</li>
            <li>temper control</li>
            <li>attitudes that support or excuse criminal behaviour</li>
          </ul>
        
  </section>
</details>

        </div>
      
    </section>

    
