          <div class="noThresholdScaleBuffer bottom-border">
            

<details class="govuk-details details--chevron-style" data-test-id="details-wrapper-images-and-indirect-contact-sexual-reoffending-predictor" id="details-images-and-indirect-contact-sexual-reoffending-predictor">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary" id="details-summary-images-and-indirect-contact-sexual-reoffending-predictor" data-test-id="details-summary">
    <span class="details__chevron" aria-hidden="true" data-test-id="details-chevron"></span>
    <span class="details__toggle-text" data-test-id="details-toggle-text">
      <span class="details__show" data-test-id="details-show">
        Show details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-show-hidden-text"> for the Images and indirect contact sexual reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
      <span class="details__hide" data-test-id="details-hide">
        Hide details
        
          <span class="govuk-visually-hidden" data-test-id="details-hide-hidden-text"> for the Images and indirect contact sexual reoffending predictor</span>
        
      </span>
    </span>
  </summary>
  <section class="govuk-details__text"
           aria-labelledby="details-summary-images-and-indirect-contact-sexual-reoffending-predictor"
           role="region"
           data-test-id="details-section">
    
            <h3>What this score predicts</h3>
            <p>The Images and indirect contact – sexual reoffending predictor predicts the risk of:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>causing or inciting a child to engage in sexual activity</li>
              <li>engaging in sexual activity in the presence of a child under 13 (offender aged 18 or over)</li>
              <li>causing a child under 13 to watch a sexual act (offender aged 18 or over)</li>
              <li>meeting a child following sexual grooming</li>
              <li>sexual communication with a child</li>
              <li>taking, permitting to be taken or making indecent photographs or pseudo photographs of children</li>
              <li>distributing or publishing indecent photographs or pseudo photographs of children</li>
              <li>possession of an indecent photograph of a child</li>
              <li>possessing prohibited images of children</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              It does not predict other sexual offences that do not involve actual or attempted physical contact with a live human victim. For example:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>possession of extreme pornographic images</li>
              <li>exposure</li>
              <li>voyeurism</li>
              <li>sending a photograph or film of genitals</li>
              <li>sharing or threatening to share an intimate photograph or film</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Further guidance about the offences it does not predict is available as an annex to the
              <a href="https://equip-portal.equip.service.justice.gov.uk/CtrlWebIsapi.dll/app/documents/091B36B5CE134AC5B45D06A30D09F8B9/master">
                Understanding risk predictors - actuarial risk assessment instruments (ARAI) user guidance (EQUip)
              </a>.
            </p>
            <h3>How we calculate the score</h3>
            <p>
              We only calculate an Images and indirect contact – sexual reoffending predictor score for men with a known history of sexual or sexually motivated offending.
            </p>
            <p>We calculate the score using the number of current and previous sanctions a person has for:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>indirect child contact offences</li>
              <li>indecent images of children offences</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Indirect contact offences are:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>causing a child to watch a sexual act</li>
              <li>causing or inciting a child to engage in sexual activity</li>
              <li>arranging child prostitution or pornography</li>
              <li>arranging or facilitating child sexual offences</li>
              <li>sexual communication with a child</li>
              <li>grooming</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The score puts the person into a risk band:</p>
            <div class="govuk-grid-row">
              <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
                <table class="govuk-table">


  <thead class="govuk-table__head">
