    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      
  <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">
    ROSH badge
    <span><strong class="govuk-tag">
  BETA
</strong>
</span>
  </h1>
  <div id="rosh-badge-wrapper" class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
      <p>The rosh badge component lets users view the band and type in a badge format. The data is from the latest completed assessment.</p>
      
      

  

  

  

  

  <div class="govuk-tabs"
    
        
        
      
        
      
    
   id="options-default-example-tabs" data-module="govuk-tabs">
  <h2 class="govuk-tabs__title">
    Contents
  </h2>

  <ul class="govuk-tabs__list">
    
          <li class="govuk-tabs__list-item govuk-tabs__list-item--selected">
      <a class="govuk-tabs__tab" href="#default-example-rendered">
        Rendered
      </a>
    </li>
      
    
          <li class="govuk-tabs__list-item">
      <a class="govuk-tabs__tab" href="#default-example-nunjucks">
        Nunjucks
      </a>
    </li>
      
    
          <li class="govuk-tabs__list-item">
      <a class="govuk-tabs__tab" href="#default-example-data">
        Data
      </a>
    </li>
      
    
  </ul>
  
      <div class="govuk-tabs__panel" id="default-example-rendered">
  
    <div class="arns-badge-base--medium"
               data-badge-base="Risk of serious harm MEDIUM">
    
            <span class="arns-badge-base__type_and_level" data-test-id="nameAndBand">Risk of serious harm <strong>MEDIUM</strong></span>
    
            
    
            
          </div>
  
  </div>
    
  
      <div class="govuk-tabs__panel govuk-tabs__panel--hidden" id="default-example-nunjucks">
  
    <p>See <a href="#options-details">Nunjucks macro options</a> for more details on how to customise component.</p>
        <pre class="app-example__code"><code>{% from &quot;arns/components/rosh-badge/macro.njk&quot; import roshBadge %}
    {{ roshBadge({data: roshDataLow }) }}</code></pre>
  
  </div>
    
  
      <div class="govuk-tabs__panel govuk-tabs__panel--hidden" id="default-example-data">
  
    <p>Data used to render this example. <strong>Use the built-in service to obtain this data from the ARNS API and pass it into every page you require to use the macros in.</strong></p>
        <pre class="app-example__code"><code>{
      &quot;roshDataLow&quot;: {
        &quot;assessment&quot;: {
          &quot;overallRisk&quot;: &quot;MEDIUM&quot;,
          &quot;completedDate&quot;: null,
          &quot;risks&quot;: []
        }
      }
    }</code></pre>
  
  </div>
    
  

</div>



      
  
  <details class="govuk-details"
    
        
        
      
        
      
    
   id="options-details">
  <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
    <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">
      Nunjucks macro options
    </span>
  </summary>
  <div class="govuk-details__text">
    
    <table class="govuk-table"
    
        
        
      
        
      
    
   id="options-table">


  <thead class="govuk-table__head">
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
    
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Name</th>
    
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Type</th>
    
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Description</th>
    
    </tr>
  </thead>

  <tbody class="govuk-table__body">

  
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
    
      
      
      <th scope="row" class="govuk-table__header">data</th>
      
    
      
      
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">object</td>
      
    
      
      
      <td class="govuk-table__cell"><strong>Required.</strong> Data from ARNS API - use service from library to obtain this (see <a href="/">Introduction</a> for more information).</td>
      
    
    </tr>
  

  </tbody>
</table>

  
  </div>
</details>


      <h2>How to use</h2>
      <p>Refer to the
        <a href="https://dsdmoj.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/NDSS/pages/4471390821/Risk+badges">Risk badges</a>
        Confluence documentation for usage details.
      </p>
      <h2>Show current (OGRS4-gen) badges for a v2 assessment (no fallback)</h2>
      <p>Display the current (OGRS4-gen) badges for the latest assessment. Note that if the assessment is legacy (v1) or there's no data for this predictor then the badges will not render. If this is not the desired behaviour you may need to add additional validation in your code.</p>
      
      

  

  

  

  

  <div class="govuk-tabs"
    
        
        
      
        
      
    
   id="options-ogrs4-no-fallback-example-tabs" data-module="govuk-tabs">
  <h2 class="govuk-tabs__title">
    Contents
  </h2>

  <ul class="govuk-tabs__list">
    
          <li class="govuk-tabs__list-item govuk-tabs__list-item--selected">
      <a class="govuk-tabs__tab" href="#ogrs4-no-fallback-example-rendered">
        Rendered
